.TH Unbin 1 "March 21, 2026" "Version 3.0" "Unbin Manual Page"
.SH NAME
Unbin \- convert text to/from binary/hex and reverse strings
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBUnbin\fR [\fI-parameter\fR] [\fItext\fR | \fI-f file\fR]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBUnbin\fR is a tool to easily convert text to binary (8-bit groups), hexadecimal (2-char groups), and vice-versa, or to reverse text strings.
It features both a Graphical User Interface (Tkinter) and a Command Line Interface.

If launched without parameters, it attempts to start the GUI. If Tkinter is not available, it falls back to an interactive terminal mode.

.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
\fB-help\fR
Show help message.
.TP
\fB-b\fR
Convert text to binary.
.TP
\fB-bt\fR
Convert binary to text.
.TP
\fB-h\fR
Convert text to hexadecimal.
.TP
\fB-ht\fR
Convert hex to text.
.TP
\fB-r\fR, \fB-rt\fR
Reverse a string.
.TP
\fB-f \fIfile\fR
Specify a file to process.
.TP
\fB-t\fR, \fB-nogui\fR
Force terminal mode.
.TP
\fB-l\fR
Print license information.
.TP
\fB-moo\fR
Easter egg.

.SH "EXAMPLES"
.TP
\fBUnbin -b "Hello"\fR
Yields: 01001000 01100101 01101100 01101100 01101111
.TP
\fBUnbin -h "Hello"\fR
Yields: 48 65 6c 6c 6f
.TP
\fBUnbin -bt "01001000 01100101"\fR
Yields: He

.SH "FILES"
.TP
\fI/usr/local/share/Unbin/Unbin\fR
Main Python script.
.TP
\fI/usr/bin/Unbin\fR
Launcher script.
.TP
\fI/usr/share/pixmaps/Unbin.tga\fR
Application icon.

